to the editor the unjustified panic buying and hoarding of cipro front page oct 16 puts an enormous pressure on practicing physicians doing a great disservice to the patients with chronic and acute illnesses dependent on cipro for life threatening emergencies in no way related to anthrax patients with chronic bronchopulmonary diseases and pseudomonas infections can not obtain the necessary antibiotic the public needs to get guidelines from the centers for disease control and prevention on how to react to this crisis lest pharmacies and hospitals run out of oral cipro for mostly unjustified reasons marcel tuchman md new york oct 17 2001 the writer is a professor of clinical medicine at new york university school of medicine

